<h2><a name="sleep" id="sleep">sleep</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>

Sleep is a C++ function that suspends the thread execution for integer value seconds.
</p>

<p>
It accepts only integer values. 
</p>

<p>
If someone wants to suspend a thread execution for a float value seconds i.e. nnn,nnn he must use a combination of sleep and <a href="usleep" class="wikilink1" title="non_standard:usleep">usleep</a>. 
</p>

